  "prompt": "My husband likes to watch movies a lot. I don't. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Find a compromise\n- Alternate between movies and activities you both enjoy\n- Agree on specific movie nights\n- Take turns choosing movies\n\n2. Make movie time more enjoyable for yourself\n- Choose movies together\n- Try different genres\n- Engage in conversation during the movie\n- Do something else nearby while he watches\n\n3. Use the time for your own activities\n- Read a book\n- Work on a hobby\n- Spend time with friends\n- Exercise\n\n4. Sometimes join him\n- Show interest in his movie preferences\n- Learn about films he likes\n- Use it as quality time together\n\n5. If it's causing relationship tension\n- Communicate openly about your feelings\n- Understand each other's perspectives\n- Find a balance that works for both of you\n\nThe key is finding a solution that respects both of your preferences and maintains a healthy relationship.",
